the electronic message<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">.9</NUMEX>
An electronic signature is a data authentication process, which
when effectively implemented, provides assurance that data
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">associated</ENAMEX> with the signature has not been altered or changed.
