(<ENAMEX TYPE="CONTACT_INFO">1</ENAMEX>) unique to the signer, (<ENAMEX TYPE="CONTACT_INFO">2</ENAMEX>) under the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">signer</ENAMEX>'s sole control,
and (<ENAMEX TYPE="CONTACT_INFO">3</ENAMEX>) capable of verification. In addition, the signature should
be linked to the data in such a manner that if the data are
changed, the signature is invalidated. The <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">National Institute of</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Standards and Technology</ENAMEX> (NIST)<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">10</TIMEX> has established procedures for
the evaluation and approval of certain automated signature
techniques11 to ensure data integrity and consistency with
previously mentioned criteria.
